The paper deals with the construction and analysis of codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The use of Gray maps and the discussion of the Griesmer bound suggest a connection to coding theory (cs.CC). The application to secret sharing schemes falls under the category of cryptography (cs.CR). The study of the Lee weight distribution and dual Lee distance involves algebraic and combinatorial methods, which are relevant to discrete mathematics (cs.DS) and theoretical computer science (cs.SI).
